   <titleInfo>
      <title>Letter, David L. Jones in Nashville, Tenn. to Anna Jones in Allegheny City, Pa, 1865 May 23</title>
   </titleInfo>
   <abstract>1865, May 23 David L. Jones in Nashville, Tenn., to his wife Anna M. Jones in Allegheny City, Pa. Continues to update her on military extremes he is experiencing. This time it is a skirmish Drill; very long and repetitive, hot, and tiring. New assignments are either made or changed daily. Once more there are rumors about when they might be leaving Nashville. Lets Anna know his plans for mailing some papers. Sends greetings to their friends, acquaintances, and family members.</abstract>
